</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-25_ pf-text-1"><strong>Accident prevention </strong>- According to the Health and Safety Executive (HSE), well-conducted risk assessments can significantly reduce the occurrence of accidents and incidents in childcare settings.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-27_ pf-text-1"><em><strong><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/childcare-and-early-years-courses-training" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span></a></strong></em><strong>Regulatory compliance</strong> - Failure to conduct proper risk assessments can result in non-compliance with the Health and Safety at Work Act 1974, leading to potential legal repercussions and damage to the setting’s reputation.





</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-29_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-30_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-31_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-33_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-34_ pf-text-1"><strong>Risk assessment</strong> - The systematic process of identifying hazards, evaluating the risks associated with those hazards, and implementing control measures to reduce or eliminate the risks.






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-36_ pf-text-1"><strong>Hazard </strong>- Anything that has the potential to cause harm, such as equipment, substances, or activities.






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-38_ pf-text-1"><strong>Risk</strong> - The likelihood that a hazard will cause harm, combined with the severity of the harm that could result.







</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-40_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-41_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-42_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practice for implementing risk assessments
</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-44_ pf-heading-1-h3">Step 1: Identify hazards
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-46_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The first step in the risk assessment process is to identify potential hazards in the setting. This involves a thorough examination of the environment, equipment, and activities. Common hazards in nurseries and early years settings include:

</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-48_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-49_ pf-text-1">Slips, trips, and falls






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-51_ pf-text-1">Unsafe play equipment



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-53_ pf-text-1"><em><strong><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/childcare-and-early-years-courses-training" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span></a></strong></em>Hazardous substances (e.g., cleaning products)





</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-55_ pf-text-1"><em><strong><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/childcare-and-early-years-courses-training" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span></a></strong></em>Inadequate supervision.







</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-57_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-58_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3">Step 2: Evaluate risks
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-61_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Once hazards have been identified, the next step is to evaluate the risks associated with them. This involves considering the likelihood of the hazard causing harm and the severity of the potential harm. Factors to consider include the age and developmental stage of the children, the layout of the setting, and the level of supervision.


</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-63_ pf-heading-1-h3">Step 3: Implement control measures
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-65_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">After evaluating the risks, it is crucial to implement appropriate control measures to reduce or eliminate the risks. Control measures can include:


</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-67_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-68_ pf-text-1">Regular maintenance and inspection of equipment.<strong>
</strong>






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-70_ pf-text-1">Implementing safe storage practices for hazardous substances.<strong>
</strong>



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-72_ pf-text-1"><em><strong><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/childcare-and-early-years-courses-training" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span></a></strong></em>Providing adequate staff training on health and safety procedures.<strong>
</strong>





</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-74_ pf-text-1"><em><strong><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/childcare-and-early-years-courses-training" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span></a></strong></em>Ensuring proper staff-to-child ratios to maintain effective supervision.<strong>
</strong>







</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-76_ pf-heading-1-h3">Step 4: Review and revise
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-78_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Risk assessments should be regularly reviewed and revised to ensure they remain effective. This includes updating the assessment whenever there are significant changes in the setting, such as new equipment, changes in staffing, or alterations to the layout.



</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-80_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-81_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-82_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-84_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-85_ pf-text-1"><strong>Training and development - </strong>Regular training on risk assessment procedures is essential for all staff. This helps to ensure that everyone is aware of potential hazards and knows how to implement control measures effectively.<strong>

</strong>






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-87_ pf-text-1"><strong>Use of technology - </strong>Leveraging technology, such as ComplyPlus™ legislation and regulatory compliance management software, can streamline the risk assessment process. This software provides a centralised platform for managing compliance, conducting assessments, and tracking updates.<strong>
</strong>



